<subSubSection id="7390DD1CCE617C428495E56EDEC580C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph id="ADD5F8B86DFA803D8C912F9653E541A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F494D1B0253FD1941352E59C7C7D4468" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Asexual morph: Conidiomata pycnidial, multi-pycnidia grouped together, globose, black, erumpent, coated with white hyphae, creamy to yellowish conidial droplets exuded from central ostioles. Conidiophores hyaline, densely aggregated, cylindrical, straight to sinuous, tapering towards the apex, 13.5-23.0 
<normalizedToken id="007CD9DCE4F4A96E248AC06DBF243B1D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.0-3.0 
<normalizedToken id="0EE88FF32EEB8815234B4B7FDE619F86" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Alpha conidiogenous cells 7.0-10 
<normalizedToken id="6CEF38B6BF1F8BFDEE9E5F2B3AC77A43" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.8-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="053D3C3CD390D5E0F58806E9E0B4D253" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, cylindrical, terminal, slightly curved. Beta conidiogenous cells 10.5-13.5 
<normalizedToken id="18562186D0000CAE44D39B6F1DCC3978" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.9-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="FD7FE0C260C6B0199E17047204825A9D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, cylindrical, hyaline, tapering towards the apex. Alpha conidia, hyaline, smooth, aseptate, ellipsoidal, multi-guttulate, apex subobtuse, base subtruncate, 4.7-5.8 
<normalizedToken id="E568EF7DDDD767BCF9BA514DBBDBA0ED" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.4-2.9 
<normalizedToken id="A7DF7756A169882587D85F4DEA653416" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(mean = 5.3 
<normalizedToken id="C515F5EA56AE1F55173EB663B0A2E25C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.6 
<normalizedToken id="8A4FDB017EA1BA8EC4E23F743451357F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20). Beta conidia hyaline, aseptate, filiform, few guttulate, slightly curved, tapering towards the both ends, 25.5-32.0 
<normalizedToken id="B8ED983789E7BF73F980F9A8B363DB96" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.0-1.6 
<normalizedToken id="2632FBB2F02EA2DE06425E487287C15A" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(mean = 27.5 
<normalizedToken id="89429D8E9E9B7FF024ACB524A08FB795" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken id="142C9E19F01E9234392435967522419B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20). Gamma conidia and sexual morph not observed.
</paragraph>
